This registration better enabled the Roman Empire to exact taxes.

Hence, Augustus unwittingly helped to fulfill a prophecy about a ruler who
would `cause an exactor to pass through the kingdom.'  The same prophecy
foretold that "the Leader of the covenant," or Messiah, would be "broken"
