@node "Installation"
@toc "Help"
@{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

  Running from floppy
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    o  You can just run the Knowledge book from this floppy disk,
       by double clicking it's icon - if you don't want to install it.

  Automatic Installation         (You need 465 Kb of free disk space)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    o  Double-click on the Install icon.

    o  Follow the on-screen instructions.

  Manual Installation
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    o  Drag the `Knowledge.Guide' file, to the destination directory
       on your hard disk, using the Workbench `drag' feature as explained
       in your instruction manual.  You do have one.... don't you? :)

    o  Drag the `MakeAssign' file into the same directory as above.

    o  Double click on the new `MakeAssign'.

    o  If you don't want to have to run `MakeAssign' all the time,
       then add this line to your S:User-startup file:

          -  Assign JW\KL: DESTINATION-DIRECTORY

       (Replacing DESTINATION-DIRECTORY, with the full path to
        the directory in which you placed `Knowledge.Guide')

  Warnings
  ~~~~~~~~
    o  When you install `Knowledge.Guide', you may crunch it if you
       wish, but if you do, you MUST ensure that the viewer you are
       using is capable of decompressing it, otherwise you will get
       rubbish!

    o  If you forget to make the assign `JW\KL:' to the directory in
       which `Knowledge.Guide' is in, you will get errors.
@endnode

@node "Problems" "Trouble-shooting - possible causes for errors"
@toc "Help"
@{b}@{u}Common Problems@{ub}@{uu}

  A requester is asking for JW\KL:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    o  You need to make an `assign' to the directory in which you have
       installed your `Knowledge.Guide' file.

    o  To do this, make sure that the file `MakeAssign' is in the same
       place, and double click it.  To make that assign permanent, see
       `Installation'.

  The contents of `Knowledge.Guide' seem scrambled
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    o  Did you compress the file?  If you did, you need to ensure that
       either:

           (a)  The file is successfully decompressed, or
           (b)  The file is uncompressed

    o  If not, try the version on the original install disk, and, if
       necessary, re-install it.

  It seems to contain funny codes, and there are no cross references
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    o  Sounds like you are using a text viewer, instead of a `Guide' one.

    o  Check that the default tool of `Knowledge.Guide' is set to
       `AmigaGuide', by clicking it's icon once, and choosing `Info' from
       the `Icon' menu.

    o  If you are without success, try the version on the original
       install disk, and re-install if necessary.
@endnode

